   This Is A Breakdown Of The Selections Available In The Level Editor :

        P          Clicking On This Allows You To Play The Level.
@{"      Move       " Link Move}  This Enables You To Move A Level To A Different Level
      Clear        This Just Clears The Levels You Select.
@{"      Erase      " Link Erase}  The Completely Erases A Level From The Levels Available.
      Swap         This Swaps The Two Levels That You Select.
@{"  Level " Link Level} @{"  Code  " Link Code}  These Will Either List The Codes Or Allow You To Enter One.
 Level Selection   To Change The Current Level Click On The Level Number.
@{"      Look       " Link Look}  This Is A Quick Way Of Looking At The Levels.
  Game Objects     The Objects In The Game Can Be Seen On The Game Help Page.
@{"      Disk       " Link Disk}  This Is Where You Load And Save Level Files.
 Time Selection    To Change The Time Allowed On A Level Click On The Numbers.

Note : Press "Esc" To Quit The Level Editor.  Remember To Save Your Work 
       First, Though !
@EndNode
@Node Move

				   Move
				   
(M)OVE Actually  Moves The  Level So If You Move Level 10 TO Level 20 Then
The Levels 11 To 20  Become Levels 10 TO 19 So  Level 11 Replaces Level 10
And Level 12 Becomes Level 11 And So On. e.g :

                   If You Move Level 4 To Level 9 Then :

			  Level 5 Becomes Level 4
			  Level 6 Becomes Level 5
			  Level 7 Becomes Level 6
			  Level 8 Becomes Level 7
			  Level 9 Becomes Level 8

		  And Then Level 4 Gets Copied Into Level 9.
 


			   @{" RETURN TO MAIN MENU " Link "Main Docs"}
@EndNode

@Node Erase

                                   Erase
				    
(E)RASE Actually Erases The Level So If You Erase Level 10 Then All Of The
Levels From 11 To 50 Are Moved Down One And Level 50 Then Gets Cleared.
If You  Wish To Insert A Level Into 10 To Make A New One Then Move 50 Into
10 Which Will Put A Clear  Level Into 10. So An Example Of ERASING A Level
Is :

                       If You Erase Level 46 Then :

			  Level 47 Becomes Level 46
			  Level 48 Becomes Level 47
			  Level 49 Becomes Level 48
			  Level 50 Becomes Level 49

			And Then Level 50 Is Cleared.


			    @{" RETURN TO MAIN MENU " Link "Main Docs"}
@EndNode

@Node Look

                                   Look
				    
(L)OOK Allows You To Quicky Go Thorough The Levels To Find A Certain Level.
To Change The Level To Look At Click On The Level Number.Once You Have Found
The Level That You Were  Looking For Then Either Press Both Mouse Buttons To
Return To The Level You Were  Last On Or Hit RETURN And This Will Put You On
The Last Level You Were LOOKing At, A Nice Idea Eeeehhhhhh.











			    @{" RETURN TO MAIN MENU " Link "Main Docs"}
@EndNode

@Node Disk

                                   Disk
				    
 (D)ISK Allows You To Load Or Save Level Files. The Options Available Are :


	 LOAD       : This Allows You To Load Almost Any Level Files.

	 SAVE       : This Saves Files To Be Reloaded Into The Level Editor.
		      Please Note That These Files Cannot Be Loaded Into The
		      Game Coin Mania - Please Use The Option Below.

	 SAVE FINAL : This Saves Files To Be Reloaded Into The Level Editor
		      Or To Be Loaded Into The Game To Be Played.
 




			    @{" RETURN TO MAIN MENU " Link "Main Docs"}
@EndNode

@Node Level

                                   Level
				    
(L)EVEL Allows You To View All The Level Codes That You Have Defined So Far.
Please Note That The Levels Will Not Save As "FINAL" If You Have Two Or More
Level Codes The Same, But An Error Message Will Come Up If This Occurs.













			    @{" RETURN TO MAIN MENU " Link "Main Docs"}
@EndNode

@Node Code

                                   Code

(C)ODE  Allows You To Enter A Level Code If That Particular Level Can Have A
Code. If You Are Not Sure Then Click On (L)EVEL And This Will List The Codes
And Which Levels Can Have Them.













			    @{" RETURN TO MAIN MENU " Link "Main Docs"}
@EndNode
